<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1733,2012]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1733,1759]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This Japanese endemic genus is recognized by the following combination of characters: Body elongateovoid, moderate in size (total length 
<quantity box="[570,711,1769,1796]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="4.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2–4.3 mm</quantity>
), with both simple and silvery lanceolate setae; basic coloration brown to dark brown; dorsum weakly shining, matte, with curly or roughly upright vestiture; labium short, shorter than antennal segment II; not exceeding mesial mesocoxa; right paramere elongate, larger than left; vesica (endosoma) broad, sigmoid, bifurcate apically; and female genital chamber with ovoid, thick-rimmed sclerotized rings and relatively developed vestibular sclerite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1733,2012]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1949,1975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2001" box="[344,491,1949,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Eremophylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,491,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Eremophylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[712,919,1949,1976]" firstAuthor="Yasunaga" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="113 - 121" refId="ref28172" refString="Yasunaga, T. (2001 a) New Phyline plant bugs from Japan (Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae). Sukunahikona, Special publication of the Japan Coleopterological Society, 1, 113 - 121." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="a">Yasunaga (2001a)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate a single representative, 
<taxonomicName authority="Yasunaga" authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Eremophylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E. hirtus</emphasis>
Yasunaga
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<specimenCount box="[458,563,1985,2012]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="male">two male</specimenCount>
specimens found from temperate deciduous forests in Honshu and Shikoku. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh &amp; Menard" box="[151,425,151,177]" firstAuthor="Schuh" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref27708" refString="Schuh, R. T. &amp; Menard, K. L. (2013) A revised classification of the Phylinae (Insecta: Heteroptera: Miridae): Arguments for the placement of genera. American Museum Novitates, 3785, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="2013">Schuh &amp; Menard (2013)</bibRefCitation>
provisionally placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2001" box="[665,812,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Eremophylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[665,812,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Eremophylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as incertae sedis within the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Douglas &amp; Scott" authorityYear="1865" box="[1184,1268,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phylini">Phylini</taxonomicName>
, as the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[289,481,187,213]" firstAuthor="Yasunaga" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="113 - 121" refId="ref28172" refString="Yasunaga, T. (2001 a) New Phyline plant bugs from Japan (Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae). Sukunahikona, Special publication of the Japan Coleopterological Society, 1, 113 - 121." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="a">Yasunaga, 2001a</bibRefCitation>
) suggested no plausible close relative. Recent field investigation by some enthusiastic colleagues yielded an additional species (
<taxonomicName authority="Yasunaga, 2022" authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2022" box="[617,772,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Orthonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nakagawai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[617,772,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E. nakagawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[779,840,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) and more than a few female specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2001" box="[1332,1429,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Eremophylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis box="[1332,1429,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E. hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which enables to posit its suprageneric placement in the subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Douglas &amp; Scott" authorityYear="1865" box="[881,1009,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Oncotylina">Oncotylina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
